50|$|The South American {{pilchard}} (Sardinops sagax) is a sardine of {{the family}} Clupeidae, {{the only member of}} the genus Sardinops. It is found in the Indo-Pacific and East Pacific oceans. Its length is up to 40 cm. It has other names, some of which more appropriately refer to subspecies, including blue pilchard, Australian pilchard (S. s. neopilchardus), blue-bait, <b>Californian</b> <b>pilchard</b> (S. s. caeruleus), Chilean sardine (S. s. sagax), Japanese pilchard (S. s. melanostictus), Pacific sardine, and Southern African pilchard (S. s. ocellatus).|$|E

